.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.TOPLAINMONTHDAY" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.toPlainMonthDay \-
Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.toPlainMonthDay()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toPlainMonthDay()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainMonthDay\f[R] object representing the
\f[CR]monthCode\f[R] and \f[CR]day\f[R] of this date in the same
calendar system.
.PP
Note that \f[CR]PlainMonthDay\f[R] objects do not have a
\f[CR]month\f[R] component, because months with the same name can have
different \f[CR]month\f[R] indexes in different years due to leap
months.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toPlainMonthDay()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainMonthDay\f[R] object representing the
\f[CR]monthCode\f[R] and \f[CR]day\f[R] of this date in the same
calendar system.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using toPlainMonthDay()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] monthDay = date.toPlainMonthDay();
console.log(monthDay.toString()); \f[I]// 07\-01\f[R]
.EE
